Package org.sbrubbles.genericcons

Class C<First,​Rest>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbrubbles.genericcons.C<First,​Rest>
  • Type Parameters:
    First - The first type.
    Rest - The last type, or a C holding the rest of the types.
    public final class C<First,​Rest>
extends Object
    Captures and represents an open-ended list of types. This class isn't supposed to be instantiated or subclassed; it's used to indicate a list in the type declaration, like below: 

     Function<?, ?> f = new Function<String, C<Object, C<Number, C<String, Integer>>>>() {
   { // the no-arg constructor
     this.types = Types.fromSuperclass(this.getClass(), 1);
   }
 };

    This list-like structure, similar to Lisp's cons, is named a cons type (hence the C), but using only one letter kept the whole structure more readable.

    Author:
    Humberto Anjos
